    <abstract id="aspace_db69b4f344a957d64d0e2faab4b1116a">LGLN was founded in New York City in 1987 to promote lesbian and gay rights in unions and labor solidarity in the gay community. Activities include the Coors Boycott Coalition, publishing Pride at Work, organizing lesbian and gay committees in unions, and resource referral, particularly regarding AIDS in the workplace and domestic partnership benefits. The collection consists mainly of research files collected by Miriam Frank and Desma Holcomb for their book, <emph render="italic">Pride at Work</emph>. Also included are the organizational files, petition files, LGLN Newsletter, DC 37 Committee, and the Lesbian and Gay Teachers Association newsletter.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_6c1a91f15d052df8fad58e429df64bcb">Materials are in English</langmaterial>
